[SN]TITLE[SN]
Manslaughter charge after crash death near Chesterfield

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 30-year-old motorcyclist has been charged with killing an elderly driver during a row about a minor crash.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stuart Bowdler, 74, collapsed following an altercation with Colin Bailey after the pair collided in Grassmoor, near Chesterfield, on Tuesday night.
Mr Bailey, from Clay Cross, Derbyshire, was charged with manslaughter and possessing controlled substances with intent to supply.
He is due to appear before magistrates later.
